From: Ilia Alshanetsky <ilia@ilia.ws>
Date: $(date +%Y-%m-%d)
Subject: [PATCH 1/5] contrib/cityhash: guard #include "config.h" for vendored builds

The vendored cityhash does an unguarded `#include "config.h"` at the top of city.cc.

clickhouse-cpp never generates that header. Any downstream that vendors the tree (especially on MSVC or in builds without an autoconf step) hits:

    fatal error C1083: Cannot open include file: 'config.h'

Guard the include with the standard `HAVE_CONFIG_H` convention. When the macro is absent, the existing fallbacks already do the right thing (little-endian detection or unconditional LE on MSVC).

No runtime change.

---
 contrib/cityhash/cityhash/city.cc | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/contrib/cityhash/cityhash/city.cc b/contrib/cityhash/cityhash/city.cc
index 8e8e0f0..e0e0e0e 100644
--- a/contrib/cityhash/cityhash/city.cc
+++ b/contrib/cityhash/cityhash/city.cc
@@ -27,7 +27,9 @@
 // writing a program that systematically explores some of the space of
 // possible hash functions, by using SIMD instructions, or by
 // compromising on hash quality.
-
-#include "config.h"
+#ifdef HAVE_CONFIG_H
+#include "config.h"
+#endif
 #include "city.h"
 
 #include <algorithm>
